🐘🦧 🌳 Maatha boy’s half way to One! 🌳🦁🦒 

Celebrating my kids birthdays, isn’t just about cakes and decor to me, it’s a part of my healing. For me it’s healing of my inner child while being everything I needed and more for my children.

As a mamma, I overthink everything. I worry every day about what would happen to them if something ever happened to me. That fear pushes me to be present, to show up, to celebrate every little and big moment in their lives. 

When my kids look back on to their childhood, I want them to know that Mamma was there for them, excited - louder than anyone else, prouder than anyone else, as their constant cheerleader - celebrating them, celebrating their every milestones, every wins - loving them endlessly. 

When they look back, i want them to see the colours - bright, warm and full of love, that they’ll cherish for a lifetime. 

Always their biggest fan, until my last breath. ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
To my dearest Maathan,

There was a day I will never forget, the day you struggled to breathe. In that moment, it felt like my own breath was taken from me. I didn’t want to live anymore. The thought of losing you shattered me in a way I didn’t know was possible. 

Tears roll down my face as I write this. There is nothing in this world as painful as losing a child. Even now, the memory brings tears to my eyes and tightens my chest. But every day since, watching you smile, laugh, and grow heals me. It gives me strength to be mamma. 

Your light lifts me from the darkest places. You are my happiness, in its purest form. Thank you for coming into our lives. Thank you for choosing me to be your mamma. You have filled our world with love in ways I could never have imagined.

With all the love in my heart,
Mamma
